Non-technical explanation - I am talking about projects which have gasless listings (do not require you to pay gas for the first listing). This essentially means the service has allowance on your tokens and you have no way to revoke it.

After seeing so many exploits of centralized marketplaces, I believe projects with default approved proxies for them should revoke the access (if possible). Only the owner of the NFT should decide who has approval on their tokens. Looking at you @psychedelic_nft.

The biggest problem of @LooksRareNFT is that listing items costs gas - barrier to entry is high. That's why the @the_x2y2 only lets you claim after you list NFTs from multiple collections. $LOOKS like they are figuring it out one strategy at a time. https://t.co/7g8fbT2hyC
